Usage: gskill install [flags]

Install all declared skills (additive, idempotent).

Examples:

    gskill install
    gskill install --agent claude,codex
    gskill install --frozen-lockfile

Flags:
  -h, --help               Show context-sensitive help.
      --json               Emit machine-readable JSON on stdout.
      --quiet              Suppress diagnostics on stderr.
      --no-interactive     Disable prompts and colored output.
      --yes                Assume yes for confirmation prompts.
      --offline            Operate without network access.
      --no-cache           Bypass the content cache.
      --dry-run            Report actions without applying them.
      --config=STRING      Path to a config file.
  -v, --verbose            Enable verbose diagnostics.
  -C, --dir=STRING         Run as if gskill started in this directory.

      --agent=AGENT,...    Target agent(s); repeatable or comma-separated.
                           This is the exact desired set: it replaces (not
                           merges with) each skill's currently recorded agents
                           — list every agent you want kept, not just the one
                           being added.
      --copy               Copy instead of symlinking (deprecated alias for
                           --install-mode copy).
      --install-mode=auto|symlink|copy
                           How skills are placed into agent directories.
      --force              Accept changed upstream content: reinstall and
                           rewrite the recorded computedHash.
      --no-init            Never auto-initialize the project; fail instead.
      --frozen-lockfile    Restore exactly from the lockfile; never modify it.
      --prune              Remove managed installs whose lock entries are gone.
